content:
Noticed when I was waiting on some builds this week, the publisher outputs a group of error messages that aren't errors. It processes everything correctly, but displays:

     [java] Error in StructureDefinition MetadataResource: Only Resource/DomainResource can be abstract
     [java] Error in StructureDefinition Resource: Unknown specialised base resource Resource
     [java] Error in StructureDefinition CanonicalResource: Only Resource/DomainResource can be abstract
     [java] Error in StructureDefinition xhtml: xhtml.id: type 'http://hl7.org/fhirpath/System.String' is not valid (a)
     [java] Error in StructureDefinition DataType: Only Element/BackboneElement can be abstract
     [java] Error in StructureDefinition PrimitiveType: Only Element/BackboneElement can be abstract
     [java] Error in StructureDefinition BackboneType: Only Element/BackboneElement can be abstract
     [java] Error in StructureDefinition Base: Only Element/BackboneElement can be abstract

Not blocking on anything, just figured most people don't read all the build output :-)
on my list to get around to correcting these
